Discription: The price at which a security first trades upon the opening of an exchange on a trading day
The highest price at which a stock traded during the course of the trading day
The lowest price at which a stock trades over the course of a trading day.
The last price at which a stock trades during a regular trading day
The closing price after adjustments for all applicable splits and dividend distributions
The number of shares of a security traded during a given period of time
